Laser Puzzle Generator
This tool is a level design helper for creating presolved laser puzzles. It is designed to help you conceptualize level designs to incorporate into games.


What does it do?
It verifies a path exists from the start to the finish.

It places blocks near the solution path to create corridors and visual noise.

Why does it exist?
Game developers can use this to quickly conceptualize layouts for puzzles that they can use in their games.

Adjustable Parameters
Map Size (6–10): Sets the grid dimensions.

Mirrors (1–10): Sets how many times the laser must bounce to reach the goal.

Obstacle Count (0–20): Sets how many extra blocks are added to distract the player.

Puzzle Seed: A 6-digit code used to recreate or share a specific layout.

How to use it
Generate: Adjust the sliders and click Generate New.

Toggle Laser: Uncheck Show Laser Path to see the puzzle as a player would.

Seed: Copy the seed to save a layout, or paste one in to load an old puzzle, as long as the other parameters are the same.

Export: Click Export JPG to save the grid as an image.